1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:04,504
[Carillo]
<i>Has Marcus Reyes gotten to you too?</i>

2
00:00:04,587 --> 00:00:07,716
<i>Are you really going to side</i>
<i>with Datu Rahman?</i>

3
00:00:07,799 --> 00:00:11,886
Are you aware
that your appointment as general

4
00:00:11,970 --> 00:00:12,971
is on the line?

5
00:00:13,054 --> 00:00:15,890
If I know something wrong
is happening around me

6
00:00:15,974 --> 00:00:17,183
and I choose to remain silent,

7
00:00:17,267 --> 00:00:20,270
that makes me even less deserving
to be a general.

8
00:00:20,770 --> 00:00:22,397
[Idris] <i>I cleaned it and kept it safe</i>

9
00:00:22,480 --> 00:00:23,648
<i>because I knew the day would come</i>

10
00:00:23,732 --> 00:00:24,816
<i>when you would need it again.</i>

11
00:00:24,899 --> 00:00:27,444
<i>You were his finest student.</i>

12
00:00:27,527 --> 00:00:29,070
<i>You also saved our island.</i>

13
00:00:29,154 --> 00:00:30,989
<i>It's only right that you inherit this.</i>

14
00:00:31,072 --> 00:00:33,450
<i>He knew that you would use it for good.</i>

15
00:00:33,533 --> 00:00:35,452
Tell me. What's your secret?

16
00:00:35,535 --> 00:00:37,495
My real name is Hassan Wadi.

17
00:00:37,579 --> 00:00:40,206
[Datu Rahman] <i>I worked</i>
<i>for Colonel Napoleon Marcelino.</i>

18
00:00:40,290 --> 00:00:43,084
He wanted to overthrow the government.

19
00:00:43,168 --> 00:00:44,836
<i>I wanted to break away,</i>

20
00:00:44,919 --> 00:00:47,380
<i>so I changed my name and started a family.</i>

21
00:00:47,464 --> 00:00:49,632
I'm the reason they're all dead.

22
00:00:49,716 --> 00:00:51,217
[Mustapha] They've been chasing you.

23
00:00:51,301 --> 00:00:53,928
Colonel Marcelino has died
a long time ago.

24
00:00:54,012 --> 00:00:54,846
But I have a feeling

25
00:00:54,929 --> 00:00:58,475
that the system he built
is still operating.

26
00:00:58,558 --> 00:00:59,559
The syndicate?

27
00:00:59,642 --> 00:01:03,897
[Carillo] <i>I'm hoping to work with you</i>
<i>until the very end.</i>

28
00:01:03,980 --> 00:01:05,899
- [exclaims]
- [gunshots]

29
00:01:07,192 --> 00:01:08,026
[Lara] <i>Sir, we have received an alert.</i>

30
00:01:08,109 --> 00:01:11,029
<i>There's an active shooting at a school--</i>
<i>East Valley Montessori.</i>

31
00:01:11,112 --> 00:01:12,363
[Azuelo] <i>I will save you!</i>

32
00:01:12,447 --> 00:01:14,407
<i>You and your friends!</i>

33
00:01:14,491 --> 00:01:15,867
<i>Set your phone to silent</i>

34
00:01:15,950 --> 00:01:18,703
and make no noise.

35
00:01:18,787 --> 00:01:21,539
- Sir.
- Call the entire… Task Force Alpha.

36
00:01:21,623 --> 00:01:26,336
<i>We're going to East Valley</i>
<i>Montessori ourselves.</i>

37
00:01:26,419 --> 00:01:27,295
<i>My son needs me!</i>

38
00:01:27,378 --> 00:01:30,006
[school bell ringing]

39
00:01:31,508 --> 00:01:37,806
[theme music playing]

40
00:01:45,980 --> 00:01:47,357
- [engine revving]
- [horn honking in distance]

41
00:01:47,440 --> 00:01:50,610
[phone ringing]

42
00:01:50,693 --> 00:01:51,528
[unsettling music playing]

43
00:01:51,611 --> 00:01:53,696
- Buddy.
- Where are you, buddy?

44
00:01:53,780 --> 00:01:55,073
I'm on my way back.

45
00:01:55,156 --> 00:01:56,574
We have an operation.

46
00:01:56,658 --> 00:01:58,368
There's a shooting incident
at East Valley.

47
00:02:00,120 --> 00:02:01,496
Hello, Agent Reyes.

48
00:02:01,579 --> 00:02:03,123
<i>Where the hell are you? Goddamn it!</i>

49
00:02:03,706 --> 00:02:05,250
<i>A lot of children will die</i>

50
00:02:05,333 --> 00:02:07,836
if we don't accomplish this mission!

51
00:02:07,919 --> 00:02:10,130
Sir, I'll just meet you at East Valley.

52
00:02:10,213 --> 00:02:11,714
Hurry up!

53
00:02:11,798 --> 00:02:12,674
Let's go.

54
00:02:12,757 --> 00:02:18,638
[unsettling music continues]

55
00:02:18,721 --> 00:02:24,853
[soft traditional music playing]

56
00:02:25,812 --> 00:02:28,481
The gun, like any other weapon,

57
00:02:29,983 --> 00:02:33,444
can mean life or death.

58
00:02:34,988 --> 00:02:36,406
It can take lives,

59
00:02:37,240 --> 00:02:39,200
but it can also save them.

60
00:02:40,076 --> 00:02:42,162
It can be a tool of oppression.

61
00:02:42,954 --> 00:02:47,417
But it can also be used
to defend yourselves

62
00:02:47,500 --> 00:02:49,168
and your loved ones.

63
00:02:52,547 --> 00:02:55,216
- [crowd clamoring]
- [school bell ringing]

64
00:02:57,385 --> 00:02:58,803
[suspenseful music playing]

65
00:02:58,887 --> 00:03:00,138
Secure the perimeter!

66
00:03:00,930 --> 00:03:03,725
Get the civilians out of here
to guarantee their safety!

67
00:03:03,808 --> 00:03:05,310
Come on! Move!

68
00:03:07,562 --> 00:03:09,355
Has the shooter been identified?

69
00:03:09,439 --> 00:03:12,025
Not yet. But we've confirmed
that he's in the main building.

70
00:03:12,108 --> 00:03:14,944
[Felix] What kind of security
does this school have?

71
00:03:15,028 --> 00:03:17,155
Why was the shooter able to get in?

72
00:03:17,238 --> 00:03:18,865
[Usman] And what's his intention
with the children?

73
00:03:18,948 --> 00:03:20,783
[Lara]
The intention doesn't matter right now.

74
00:03:20,867 --> 00:03:22,076
What matters is that we evacuate

75
00:03:22,160 --> 00:03:23,912
every single person here,
including the shooter.

76
00:03:23,995 --> 00:03:26,331
[suspenseful music continues]

77
00:03:26,414 --> 00:03:27,999
[Felix] You! Hey, hey!

78
00:03:28,082 --> 00:03:29,250
Guard!

79
00:03:29,334 --> 00:03:32,003
Why was someone with a gun
allowed to get in?

80
00:03:32,086 --> 00:03:34,255
You're not doing your job properly!

81
00:03:34,339 --> 00:03:36,424
You should be fired!

82
00:03:36,507 --> 00:03:38,426
- [Marcus] That's enough.
- You're a lazy bum!

83
00:03:38,509 --> 00:03:40,720
- I said, that's enough.
- I'm just telling the truth.

84
00:03:40,803 --> 00:03:43,097
We need information on the shooter.

85
00:03:43,181 --> 00:03:44,682
His age, his history,

86
00:03:44,766 --> 00:03:48,061
and what motivated him
to target the students.

87
00:03:48,144 --> 00:03:49,270
Uh, sir.

88
00:03:49,354 --> 00:03:51,147
I overheard your conversation.

89
00:03:51,231 --> 00:03:52,732
The truth is,

90
00:03:52,815 --> 00:03:55,068
the shooter is also one of our students.

91
00:03:55,151 --> 00:03:56,527
[suspenseful music continues]

92
00:03:57,111 --> 00:03:58,071
What happened?

93
00:03:58,154 --> 00:04:00,490
I was in the corridor earlier. I don't…

94
00:04:00,573 --> 00:04:02,408
…know how he was able to get a gun.

95
00:04:02,492 --> 00:04:03,868
He's a high school student, sir.

96
00:04:03,952 --> 00:04:06,287
I saw him. He fired the gun.

97
00:04:06,871 --> 00:04:07,914
[Marcus] Was he with someone?

98
00:04:07,997 --> 00:04:09,249
It was only him, sir.

99
00:04:09,332 --> 00:04:10,708
Thank you.

100
00:04:10,792 --> 00:04:13,044
This is a big help. Get going now.

101
00:04:13,127 --> 00:04:18,508
- [overlapping shouting]
- [suspenseful music continues]

102
00:04:21,469 --> 00:04:23,263
[Marcus] We apologize to everyone.

103
00:04:23,346 --> 00:04:26,432
Please do not go
beyond the perimeter area.

104
00:04:26,516 --> 00:04:27,600
We are asking for your cooperation.

105
00:04:27,684 --> 00:04:30,270
We understand that you are worried.

106
00:04:30,353 --> 00:04:33,147
However, we cannot act
recklessly right now.

107
00:04:33,231 --> 00:04:34,399
The shooter is a young man,

108
00:04:34,482 --> 00:04:35,984
and it is certain that he is unstable.

109
00:04:36,067 --> 00:04:38,820
We must not allow anyone else to get hurt.

110
00:04:38,903 --> 00:04:41,322
Let us do our job.

111
00:04:41,406 --> 00:04:45,201
We will do everything we can
to ensure that your children

112
00:04:45,285 --> 00:04:47,036
are brought out safely.

113
00:04:48,413 --> 00:04:49,580
Again, we are sorry.

114
00:04:49,664 --> 00:04:52,000
We are simply doing our duty.

115
00:04:52,083 --> 00:04:53,293
Please remain here.

116
00:04:53,376 --> 00:04:55,503
[overlapping chattering]

117
00:04:55,586 --> 00:04:57,255
Marcus! Erick is inside!

118
00:04:57,338 --> 00:04:58,840
- Jean…
- [sobs]

119
00:04:58,923 --> 00:05:02,927
Please! I can't lose my son,
not after losing Oliver!

120
00:05:03,011 --> 00:05:04,679
[school bell ringing continues]

121
00:05:04,762 --> 00:05:06,180
[labored breathing]

122
00:05:06,264 --> 00:05:07,974
[Oliver] Before it's too late,

123
00:05:08,057 --> 00:05:10,018
let my family know…

124
00:05:10,768 --> 00:05:13,479
I love them, and I'll always be with them.

125
00:05:14,897 --> 00:05:16,024
Where's Erick?

126
00:05:16,733 --> 00:05:19,068
Do you know his exact location?
Where's his classroom?

127
00:05:19,944 --> 00:05:21,446
The tracking device!

128
00:05:21,529 --> 00:05:25,074
Uh, Oliver taught him to always wear it

129
00:05:25,158 --> 00:05:26,326
in case of an emergency.

130
00:05:26,409 --> 00:05:27,702
Uh…

131
00:05:27,785 --> 00:05:29,287
It's right here.

132
00:05:29,370 --> 00:05:30,872
[suspenseful music continues]

133
00:05:34,208 --> 00:05:35,126
[device pinging]

134
00:05:35,209 --> 00:05:36,461
Thanks, Jean.

135
00:05:36,544 --> 00:05:37,628
[Marcus] I got it.

136
00:05:38,212 --> 00:05:40,256
- Thank you, sir Marcus.
- Don't worry.

137
00:05:40,339 --> 00:05:42,133
I'm going to save Erick.

138
00:05:42,216 --> 00:05:44,260
I promise you. I'll save him.

139
00:05:44,343 --> 00:05:46,137
Thank you so much, sir.

140
00:05:47,889 --> 00:05:50,892
[Erick] Mommy, daddy!

141
00:05:50,975 --> 00:05:54,979
[sobbing]

142
00:05:55,688 --> 00:05:56,981
[Marcus] Lara.

143
00:05:57,940 --> 00:06:00,985
I need you to stay here
to handle the situation.

144
00:06:01,069 --> 00:06:02,737
Listen up, everyone.

145
00:06:02,820 --> 00:06:05,156
So far, this is all
we know about the shooter.

146
00:06:05,239 --> 00:06:06,949
He's a minor, a high school student.

147
00:06:07,033 --> 00:06:08,993
He's alone and is probably unstable--

148
00:06:09,077 --> 00:06:11,829
What is taking you so long?!

149
00:06:11,913 --> 00:06:13,372
- Sir, sir.
- Sir…

150
00:06:13,456 --> 00:06:15,500
Let me in! Kyle is inside!

151
00:06:15,583 --> 00:06:17,460
- Sir, I'm sorry.
- Sir…

152
00:06:17,960 --> 00:06:20,129
Reyes, I am your boss.

153
00:06:20,213 --> 00:06:22,090
So let me in. Goddamn it!

154
00:06:22,173 --> 00:06:24,217
Sir, you're too emotional right now.

155
00:06:24,300 --> 00:06:26,260
If you go in like that,

156
00:06:26,344 --> 00:06:28,679
you might put your son at greater risk.

157
00:06:28,763 --> 00:06:30,473
[Marcus] You have to trust us.

158
00:06:30,556 --> 00:06:32,391
We'll save your child.

159
00:06:32,475 --> 00:06:34,185
It's best if you stay here, sir.

160
00:06:34,268 --> 00:06:37,313
Try to get in touch with him.
Find out his exact location.

161
00:06:37,396 --> 00:06:39,273
Sir, please.

162
00:06:40,066 --> 00:06:41,818
We'll handle going in ourselves.

163
00:06:41,901 --> 00:06:44,153
[gloomy music playing]

164
00:06:48,825 --> 00:06:51,452
Save my son, Reyes.

165
00:06:52,578 --> 00:06:55,206
Bring Kyle back to me, please.

166
00:06:55,873 --> 00:06:57,375
You can count on it, sir.

167
00:06:57,458 --> 00:06:59,836
[school bell ringing continues]

168
00:07:02,505 --> 00:07:07,969
[gloomy music continues]

169
00:07:08,052 --> 00:07:13,015
[Jalil] I'm going to show you how to load,
ready,

170
00:07:13,975 --> 00:07:17,437
and fire it correctly.

171
00:07:17,520 --> 00:07:19,605
[pensive music playing]

172
00:07:19,689 --> 00:07:20,898
I'll teach you all of this

173
00:07:20,982 --> 00:07:24,360
so you'll know how to defend yourselves,

174
00:07:24,444 --> 00:07:26,154
especially when I'm not around.

175
00:07:29,657 --> 00:07:31,993
We must do this
to prevent another tragedy.

176
00:07:33,828 --> 00:07:35,580
[Ramli] We understand, Jalil.

177
00:07:37,540 --> 00:07:43,421
Our objective is to get
the innocent students to safety

178
00:07:43,504 --> 00:07:45,756
and to pacify and apprehend the shooter.

179
00:07:45,840 --> 00:07:49,218
As much as possible,
we must avoid using use guns.

180
00:07:49,302 --> 00:07:52,638
The goal of this mission
is zero casualties.

181
00:07:52,722 --> 00:07:53,890
Understood?

182
00:07:53,973 --> 00:07:55,391
- Yes, sir!
- Yes, sir!

183
00:07:56,058 --> 00:07:57,143
Let's move.

184
00:07:57,226 --> 00:08:02,064
[thrilling music playing]

185
00:08:02,148 --> 00:08:03,274
[crowd clamoring]

186
00:08:03,357 --> 00:08:04,984
[crowd clamoring]

187
00:08:05,067 --> 00:08:07,987
[crowd clamoring]

188
00:08:08,070 --> 00:08:12,241
[parent] Our children's lives
are in danger! Do something!

189
00:08:12,325 --> 00:08:14,368
We've been here long enough already!

190
00:08:14,452 --> 00:08:19,999
- [all sobbing]
- [school bell ringing]

191
00:08:24,378 --> 00:08:27,089
[both crying]

192
00:08:28,424 --> 00:08:29,884
Grab your weapons.

193
00:08:29,967 --> 00:08:34,430
[dark music playing]

194
00:08:45,525 --> 00:08:47,068
[Jalil] This is a magazine.

195
00:08:47,652 --> 00:08:49,195
Take a look at your magazines.

196
00:08:49,946 --> 00:08:51,739
Make sure they're always loaded.

197
00:08:51,822 --> 00:08:52,907
Am I clear?

198
00:08:53,950 --> 00:08:55,868
This is how you insert a magazine.

199
00:08:56,452 --> 00:08:58,829
Make sure it's locked in place.
Then, ready the weapon.

200
00:08:58,913 --> 00:09:01,249
[guns cocking]

201
00:09:01,332 --> 00:09:02,792
[dark music continues]

202
00:09:02,875 --> 00:09:04,460
Clear?

203
00:09:04,544 --> 00:09:05,711
- [man] Yes.
- [woman] Absolutely.

204
00:09:05,795 --> 00:09:08,130
Now you understand how important it is

205
00:09:08,214 --> 00:09:11,509
- to know how to use a gun.
- [Harun] Jalil! Jalil!

206
00:09:12,635 --> 00:09:13,678
Jalil!

207
00:09:14,762 --> 00:09:16,138
Jalil!

208
00:09:16,222 --> 00:09:18,558
Oh, what happened?

209
00:09:19,600 --> 00:09:21,477
Armed men are coming.

210
00:09:21,561 --> 00:09:24,480
[tense music playing]

211
00:09:24,564 --> 00:09:26,190
- What are we going to do?
- This is big trouble.

212
00:09:26,274 --> 00:09:27,400
Jalil.

213
00:09:29,485 --> 00:09:30,820
[Jalil] Hide yourselves!

214
00:09:31,654 --> 00:09:32,822
Hide now, hurry!

215
00:09:32,905 --> 00:09:36,617
- Hide over there!
- You guys, get rid of that!

216
00:09:36,701 --> 00:09:38,369
- Remove everything, now!
- Come on, let's hide!

217
00:09:38,452 --> 00:09:40,663
- Go, go!
- Faster! Hurry up!

218
00:09:40,746 --> 00:09:42,206
- Over there!
- Move it!

219
00:09:42,290 --> 00:09:43,916
Get out of here and hide!

220
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:48,421
[tense music continues]

221
00:09:54,510 --> 00:09:55,678
[gun cocks]

222
00:10:00,725 --> 00:10:04,395
[music swelling]

223
00:10:05,730 --> 00:10:06,772
You two, head over there!

224
00:10:06,856 --> 00:10:08,441
- You, go that way!
- [goon 1] Come on!

225
00:10:08,524 --> 00:10:11,736
- [heavy footsteps]
- [suspenseful music playing]

226
00:10:18,284 --> 00:10:19,535
Where's everyone?

227
00:10:20,661 --> 00:10:22,997
Boss, maybe they all ran away!

228
00:10:24,540 --> 00:10:25,958
Good.

229
00:10:26,042 --> 00:10:27,793
Now we can proceed smoothly.

230
00:10:28,377 --> 00:10:30,546
Nothing stands in our way
of securing the weapons.

231
00:10:32,548 --> 00:10:33,549
Let's go!

232
00:10:35,760 --> 00:10:37,428
[alarm blaring]

233
00:10:37,511 --> 00:10:42,475
[suspenseful music continues]

234
00:10:43,684 --> 00:10:44,644
[device chimes]

235
00:10:48,314 --> 00:10:50,691
[Marcus]
<i>I wasn't able to save you, Oliver.</i>

236
00:10:50,775 --> 00:10:52,234
<i>But I promise you this:</i>

237
00:10:52,318 --> 00:10:54,654
<i>I won't let you down this time.</i>

238
00:11:00,076 --> 00:11:04,455
<i>I won't stop until I find</i>
<i>and save your son.</i>

239
00:11:09,460 --> 00:11:15,591
[alarm blaring continues]

240
00:11:15,674 --> 00:11:21,597
[suspenseful music continues]

241
00:11:30,898 --> 00:11:32,817
[sobbing]

242
00:11:32,900 --> 00:11:35,152
Mommy! Daddy!

243
00:11:36,028 --> 00:11:36,987
[device pinging]

244
00:11:44,286 --> 00:11:46,831
[alarm blaring continues]

245
00:11:46,914 --> 00:11:50,251
[suspenseful music continues]

246
00:11:50,334 --> 00:11:53,003
- [Erick sobbing]
- [device pinging rapidly]

247
00:11:53,796 --> 00:11:55,631
- [high-pitched ringing]
- [breathing raggedly]

248
00:11:58,134 --> 00:11:59,343
Daddy?

249
00:12:01,262 --> 00:12:02,513
Erick.

250
00:12:03,347 --> 00:12:05,266
- Uncle!
- Erick!

251
00:12:07,476 --> 00:12:08,561
Erick…

252
00:12:08,644 --> 00:12:12,648
- [breathing heavily]
- [crying]

253
00:12:12,731 --> 00:12:16,235
Don't cry anymore. I'm here.

254
00:12:16,318 --> 00:12:18,070
I'll always be here.

255
00:12:18,154 --> 00:12:21,323
You're safe now, okay? You're safe.

256
00:12:22,074 --> 00:12:25,119
[sobbing]

257
00:12:25,202 --> 00:12:26,662
[suspenseful music continues]

258
00:12:27,329 --> 00:12:30,624
[mumbling]

259
00:12:30,708 --> 00:12:32,042
[whispers] Come with me, now!

260
00:12:33,127 --> 00:12:34,378
- [Marcus grunts]
- [Erick sobs]

261
00:12:38,549 --> 00:12:40,968
[alarm blaring continues]

262
00:12:41,051 --> 00:12:43,804
[sniffling, sobbing]

263
00:12:43,888 --> 00:12:50,478
[suspenseful music continues]

264
00:12:50,561 --> 00:12:55,483
[sniffling, mumbling]

265
00:12:59,195 --> 00:13:02,031
[Marcus breathing heavily]

266
00:13:04,867 --> 00:13:08,329
Erick, I want you to go with him.

267
00:13:08,412 --> 00:13:11,123
He'll bring you to your mom, okay?

268
00:13:11,207 --> 00:13:13,167
- Yes, Uncle.
- Go now.

269
00:13:13,250 --> 00:13:16,128
- Buddy, take care of him.
- Be careful.

270
00:13:16,212 --> 00:13:18,714
Calm down. Get moving.
You'll be reunited with your mother soon.

271
00:13:20,758 --> 00:13:22,301
[Jalil] Get out of here.

272
00:13:23,469 --> 00:13:26,013
There's nothing here for you.

273
00:13:26,847 --> 00:13:30,851
We decide whether we get
something out of a place.

274
00:13:30,935 --> 00:13:32,269
Not you!

275
00:13:32,937 --> 00:13:37,650
I'm warning you: leave now,
before anyone gets hurt.

276
00:13:38,567 --> 00:13:41,195
[tense music playing]

277
00:13:41,278 --> 00:13:42,238
Us?

278
00:13:43,030 --> 00:13:44,073
You'll hurt us?

279
00:13:46,575 --> 00:13:48,118
There are eight of us.

280
00:13:48,202 --> 00:13:49,328
But you?

281
00:13:51,080 --> 00:13:52,665
You're on your own.

282
00:13:54,959 --> 00:13:56,001
[blade whooshing]

283
00:13:56,085 --> 00:13:59,797
[tense music continues]

284
00:13:59,880 --> 00:14:02,007
Where's your tough-guy act now?

285
00:14:02,091 --> 00:14:03,842
Where's your backup?

286
00:14:04,843 --> 00:14:06,345
Did they run away?

287
00:14:06,428 --> 00:14:07,930
Go into hiding?

288
00:14:08,013 --> 00:14:09,473
I thought the Tausug people were brave.

289
00:14:09,557 --> 00:14:11,100
What happened to the Muslims?

290
00:14:11,183 --> 00:14:13,894
Where are they now, huh?

291
00:14:13,978 --> 00:14:15,604
They left you alone to fight.

292
00:14:15,688 --> 00:14:17,690
[tense music continues]

293
00:14:19,817 --> 00:14:20,734
[neighbor 1] We're here!

294
00:14:23,070 --> 00:14:24,572
[neighbor 2] He's not alone!

295
00:14:25,406 --> 00:14:27,116
- Go on, try to harm him!
- We're ready to fight!

296
00:14:27,199 --> 00:14:28,909
We're not afraid of you!

297
00:14:33,998 --> 00:14:38,377
[tense music continues]

298
00:14:41,672 --> 00:14:45,217
[school bell ringing]

299
00:14:45,301 --> 00:14:48,846
[unsettling music playing]

300
00:15:27,718 --> 00:15:28,844
CJ!

301
00:15:29,553 --> 00:15:30,596
Jack!

302
00:15:31,847 --> 00:15:32,932
- CJ!
- Where…

303
00:15:33,015 --> 00:15:35,351
Where are you? Wait for me!

304
00:15:35,434 --> 00:15:36,435
Wait for me!

305
00:15:40,064 --> 00:15:43,233
- [shouts angrily] CJ!
- D-don't do this, please!

306
00:15:43,317 --> 00:15:47,279
[unsettling music continues]

307
00:15:48,030 --> 00:15:50,699
- No-- Please, don't…
- This is all your fault!

308
00:15:51,450 --> 00:15:53,827
I never did anything wrong
to you or your friends.

309
00:15:56,121 --> 00:15:57,623
But what did you do?

310
00:15:57,706 --> 00:15:59,249
You always set out to humiliate me.

311
00:16:00,376 --> 00:16:03,379
You always hurt me,
you always made fun of me!

312
00:16:03,462 --> 00:16:05,381
[CJ sobbing]

313
00:16:05,464 --> 00:16:08,634
You made my life a living hell.

314
00:16:08,717 --> 00:16:10,260
- [sobbing]
- [sniffling]

315
00:16:10,344 --> 00:16:12,471
You ruined my life!

316
00:16:12,554 --> 00:16:17,309
[unsettling music continues]

317
00:16:20,771 --> 00:16:23,524
[CJ] Gab, please. I'm begging you. No…

318
00:16:23,607 --> 00:16:25,234
Don't do this.

319
00:16:31,115 --> 00:16:32,992
We don't want any trouble,

320
00:16:34,076 --> 00:16:36,662
but we don't back down from anything.

321
00:16:36,745 --> 00:16:41,208
So I'll repeat myself: leave this island!

322
00:16:41,291 --> 00:16:44,378
[tense music playing]

323
00:16:44,461 --> 00:16:45,963
[gunshots]

324
00:16:48,215 --> 00:16:49,299
[Jalil grunts]

325
00:16:49,383 --> 00:16:51,385
- [grunting]
- [blade hisses]

326
00:16:55,055 --> 00:16:56,056
[goon 1] Stop!

327
00:16:56,140 --> 00:16:57,474
We surrender!

328
00:16:57,558 --> 00:16:58,642
- [goon 2] You win!
- [goon 3] We give up!

329
00:16:58,726 --> 00:17:00,561
We're not going to fight you!

330
00:17:00,644 --> 00:17:03,814
- No, let's finish them!
- We surrender!

331
00:17:03,897 --> 00:17:05,357
- Take their weapons!
- We give up!

332
00:17:05,441 --> 00:17:07,317
- Get them, come on!
- [Jalil] Stop!

333
00:17:07,401 --> 00:17:08,610
Hang on!

334
00:17:08,694 --> 00:17:10,946
Calm down, everyone.

335
00:17:11,822 --> 00:17:13,073
We already won.

336
00:17:14,533 --> 00:17:18,495
We already won.
There's no need to stoop to their level.

337
00:17:19,663 --> 00:17:23,333
We can show mercy,

338
00:17:23,417 --> 00:17:25,377
even to our enemies.

339
00:17:25,461 --> 00:17:27,588
[tense music continues]

340
00:17:27,671 --> 00:17:31,300
Especially when they can't
defend themselves.

341
00:17:31,383 --> 00:17:32,342
[goon 1] Thank you.

342
00:17:32,426 --> 00:17:34,762
Don't ever come back here.
Do you understand?

343
00:17:34,845 --> 00:17:37,014
- Yes.
- Because next time,

344
00:17:37,556 --> 00:17:40,017
mercy won't be an option.

345
00:17:40,601 --> 00:17:42,561
Tell your friends…

346
00:17:43,145 --> 00:17:45,898
to leave Damai Island alone.

347
00:17:45,981 --> 00:17:50,486
The people here can protect themselves.

348
00:17:51,236 --> 00:17:52,863
Get lost.

349
00:17:52,946 --> 00:17:53,989
Scram!

350
00:17:54,073 --> 00:17:55,824
- Don't show your faces again!
- Get away from here!

351
00:17:55,908 --> 00:17:58,118
- Stay gone!
- Don't come back!

352
00:17:59,203 --> 00:18:00,496
Jalil, thank you!

353
00:18:00,579 --> 00:18:02,206
[in Tausug] Thank you, Jalil.

354
00:18:02,289 --> 00:18:04,166
- Thank you!
- We owe you a lot!

355
00:18:04,249 --> 00:18:05,751
- Jalil, thank you!
- We defended ourselves!

356
00:18:05,834 --> 00:18:07,878
Did anyone get hurt? Shot?

357
00:18:07,961 --> 00:18:09,838
[in Arabic] Praise be to God,
everyone is safe.

358
00:18:10,547 --> 00:18:12,382
- Praise be!
- Praise be!

359
00:18:12,466 --> 00:18:13,675
[in Arabic] God is great!

360
00:18:13,759 --> 00:18:15,552
- Praise be to Allah!
- Praise be to Allah!

361
00:18:15,636 --> 00:18:16,762
[in Arabic] God is great!

362
00:18:16,845 --> 00:18:18,097
[in unison in Arabic] God is great!

363
00:18:18,180 --> 00:18:20,349
- [in Arabic] God is great!
- [in unison in Arabic] God is great!

364
00:18:20,432 --> 00:18:22,893
- [in Arabic] God is great!
- [in unison in Arabic] God is great!

365
00:18:22,976 --> 00:18:25,771
[dramatic music playing]

366
00:18:25,854 --> 00:18:28,899
- [suspenseful music playing]
- [teen sobbing in distance]

367
00:18:29,942 --> 00:18:34,696
[school bell ringing]

368
00:18:37,908 --> 00:18:39,159
Gab?

369
00:18:44,581 --> 00:18:47,167
[CJ sobs] Don't do this, please.

370
00:18:47,251 --> 00:18:49,002
[CJ, Gab sobbing]

371
00:18:49,086 --> 00:18:51,713
Gab, stop this! Please!

372
00:18:51,797 --> 00:18:54,466
Put down the gun! Don't do this!

373
00:18:54,550 --> 00:18:56,844
Get out of here, Kyle! For your own good!

374
00:18:56,927 --> 00:18:59,138
[suspenseful music continues]

375
00:18:59,221 --> 00:19:00,681
[baseball bat clatters]

376
00:19:00,764 --> 00:19:01,932
Gab!

377
00:19:03,183 --> 00:19:06,812
Let's go! Come with me!
Let's leave this place together!

378
00:19:07,938 --> 00:19:10,774
No! Why would I?

379
00:19:11,608 --> 00:19:13,318
They already ruined my life!

380
00:19:13,402 --> 00:19:14,653
[Kyle] Gab, please!

381
00:19:14,736 --> 00:19:16,405
[suspenseful music continues]

382
00:19:16,488 --> 00:19:18,157
You, CJ!

383
00:19:18,240 --> 00:19:20,284
You, Miggy, and Jack!

384
00:19:22,452 --> 00:19:25,497
You're the ones who wrecked everything!

385
00:19:29,293 --> 00:19:30,794
[hurried footsteps]

386
00:19:30,878 --> 00:19:32,713
- Sir, sir, sir! Sir!
- [Sean] Head to the exit.

387
00:19:33,839 --> 00:19:35,048
At the end of the hallway!

388
00:19:35,132 --> 00:19:36,592
There's a student who was shot!

389
00:19:36,675 --> 00:19:38,677
His name is Miggy, a bully!

390
00:19:38,760 --> 00:19:40,929
[Miggy wailing] Help!

391
00:19:41,013 --> 00:19:42,639
[suspenseful music continues]

392
00:19:42,723 --> 00:19:44,224
- [Felix] Wait a second.
- [sobbing] Help!

393
00:19:44,308 --> 00:19:46,476
- [school bell ringing]
- [panicked breathing]

394
00:19:47,853 --> 00:19:49,771
- A bully?
- Yes, sir.

395
00:19:49,855 --> 00:19:52,149
He's one of the bullies
who kept targeting Gab.

396
00:19:52,733 --> 00:19:54,484
That's probably why Gab did this.

397
00:19:54,568 --> 00:19:56,069
He's over there!

398
00:19:56,945 --> 00:19:58,197
[young Felix] <i>Enough, let me go!</i>

399
00:19:58,280 --> 00:20:00,240
<i>- Stop resisting! Come with us!</i>
<i>- Get your hands off me!</i>

400
00:20:00,324 --> 00:20:02,743
- [blows landing]
- [grunting]

401
00:20:02,826 --> 00:20:04,870
[indistinct shouting]

402
00:20:04,953 --> 00:20:05,913
- [groans]
- [laughter]

403
00:20:05,996 --> 00:20:06,914
[man] <i>That's what you deserve!</i>

404
00:20:06,997 --> 00:20:08,790
- [laughter]
- [man] <i>Come on!</i>

405
00:20:11,293 --> 00:20:12,878
Alright, we'll handle this.
Go to the exit.

406
00:20:16,632 --> 00:20:17,633
Sir, let's go.

407
00:20:20,719 --> 00:20:21,887
Are you okay, sir?

408
00:20:24,223 --> 00:20:25,265
Yes.

409
00:20:25,349 --> 00:20:26,642
Come on, let's go up.

410
00:20:27,434 --> 00:20:28,518
Quick!

411
00:20:32,522 --> 00:20:34,691
[whimpers] Help!

412
00:20:34,775 --> 00:20:36,485
Help me!

413
00:20:37,486 --> 00:20:38,820
Help!

414
00:20:40,113 --> 00:20:42,324
Please, help me. Help me.

415
00:20:42,407 --> 00:20:43,825
- Please, help me.
- Just relax for now, okay?

416
00:20:43,909 --> 00:20:45,202
- Help me. [pants]
- Yes, yes. I'm here.

417
00:20:45,285 --> 00:20:48,038
- You're going to be okay.
- Am I going to die? Help me!

418
00:20:48,121 --> 00:20:50,374
You need to relax. You need to relax.

419
00:20:50,457 --> 00:20:52,793
- Help me, help me.
- Yes, yes.

420
00:20:52,876 --> 00:20:54,336
Help me-- [whimpers]

421
00:20:54,419 --> 00:20:55,629
Hey, shut up.

422
00:20:55,712 --> 00:20:56,964
[coughs, whimpers]

423
00:20:57,047 --> 00:20:59,132
You're such a bully.

424
00:20:59,216 --> 00:21:01,093
Now you're crying?

425
00:21:02,010 --> 00:21:04,263
- It's nothing, look.
- [wails]

426
00:21:04,346 --> 00:21:05,973
- It's just a graze.
- [cries]

427
00:21:06,056 --> 00:21:07,474
Far from anything serious.

428
00:21:07,557 --> 00:21:09,559
[cries, sobs]

429
00:21:09,643 --> 00:21:11,728
- Look at me. Look at me.
- Help me, I'm going to die.

430
00:21:11,812 --> 00:21:12,938
- You're going to be okay.
- Help me!

431
00:21:13,021 --> 00:21:15,357
- Sir, please. Please.
- You're going to be okay.

432
00:21:15,440 --> 00:21:17,651
- I need you to relax.
- Please, help me.

433
00:21:17,734 --> 00:21:19,903
Please. Help me… [pants]

434
00:21:19,987 --> 00:21:22,072
- You're going to be okay.
- [Liam] Hold it like this.

435
00:21:22,155 --> 00:21:23,991
- There, just like that.
- [grunts, whimpers]

436
00:21:25,033 --> 00:21:27,619
[Liam] Good job, good job.
You're okay. Very good, very good.

437
00:21:27,703 --> 00:21:29,246
I'm going to be okay.

438
00:21:29,329 --> 00:21:31,540
Yes, yes. Look at me. Relax.

439
00:21:31,623 --> 00:21:35,043
[crowd shouting indistinctly]

440
00:21:38,297 --> 00:21:39,673
My son! [whimpers]

441
00:21:39,756 --> 00:21:42,342
Erick! Erick! Erick!

442
00:21:42,426 --> 00:21:43,760
[cries] Erick!

443
00:21:43,844 --> 00:21:45,262
- [sobs] Erick!
- Mommy!

444
00:21:45,345 --> 00:21:47,222
[whimpers]

445
00:21:47,306 --> 00:21:49,474
[crying]

446
00:21:50,892 --> 00:21:52,269
Are you okay? [sobs]

447
00:21:53,979 --> 00:21:55,772
- Kyle…
- [line ringing]

448
00:21:55,856 --> 00:21:56,732
Where are you, son?

449
00:21:56,815 --> 00:21:58,567
[line ringing]

450
00:21:58,650 --> 00:22:00,110
- Pick up!
- [line ringing]

451
00:22:02,195 --> 00:22:03,405
[Kyle] Gab…

452
00:22:03,488 --> 00:22:05,032
Please, stop.

453
00:22:05,949 --> 00:22:07,659
Just surrender, Gab! Please!

454
00:22:08,660 --> 00:22:10,746
I'll talk to Dad, I'll go with you.

455
00:22:10,829 --> 00:22:13,248
[tense music playing]

456
00:22:13,332 --> 00:22:15,542
He will believe you.
He will understand you.

457
00:22:15,625 --> 00:22:18,128
[stammers] Y-you won't understand me.

458
00:22:18,962 --> 00:22:21,631
Because you're not the ones
being bullied by those three!

459
00:22:23,759 --> 00:22:25,635
You don't experience it!

460
00:22:27,512 --> 00:22:31,349
[Azuelo] <i>They're just teasing you.</i>
<i>You fought back. Just ignore them.</i>

461
00:22:31,433 --> 00:22:33,518
[Kyle] <i>Dad, how can I ignore it?</i>

462
00:22:33,602 --> 00:22:35,854
<i>They're saying all kinds</i>
<i>of things about you.</i>

463
00:22:36,438 --> 00:22:39,066
<i>They told me you're a useless cop.</i>

464
00:22:39,858 --> 00:22:41,610
<i>How am I supposed to accept that?</i>

465
00:22:42,694 --> 00:22:44,863
<i>That Datu Rahman got away from you…</i>

466
00:22:46,198 --> 00:22:47,407
<i>…because you're weak.</i>

467
00:22:48,283 --> 00:22:49,701
<i>Because you're not good.</i>

468
00:22:49,785 --> 00:22:51,453
[Kyle sobbing]

469
00:22:51,536 --> 00:22:53,413
<i>Because you're not smart.</i>

470
00:22:54,623 --> 00:22:55,624
[sniffles]

471
00:22:55,707 --> 00:22:57,042
<i>I can't bear to hear that, Pa.</i>

472
00:22:57,125 --> 00:22:58,668
[tense music playing]

473
00:23:01,046 --> 00:23:02,714
Believe me, Gab.

474
00:23:04,049 --> 00:23:05,884
I understand you!

475
00:23:06,676 --> 00:23:09,012
And I'm sure Dad will understand you too!

476
00:23:09,096 --> 00:23:12,516
So please, don't do this.
He won't judge you.

477
00:23:14,976 --> 00:23:17,562
[Gab crying, whimpering]

478
00:23:18,438 --> 00:23:21,608
[tense music continues]

479
00:23:25,237 --> 00:23:26,530
- [gun thuds]
- [grunts]

480
00:23:26,613 --> 00:23:28,156
[grunting]

481
00:23:28,240 --> 00:23:29,574
- [cries]
- Gab, stop it!

482
00:23:29,658 --> 00:23:30,492
- Stop it!
- [grunts]

483
00:23:30,575 --> 00:23:31,910
[line ringing]

484
00:23:31,993 --> 00:23:33,578
Pick up your phone, son. Come on.

485
00:23:33,662 --> 00:23:35,038
- [cries]
- Let it go!

486
00:23:35,122 --> 00:23:35,956
I'm going to do this!

487
00:23:36,039 --> 00:23:38,708
- I'm going to do this!
- Please, that's enough!

488
00:23:38,792 --> 00:23:40,752
[line ringing]

489
00:23:40,836 --> 00:23:44,172
- Hurry! Hurry up.
- [kids screaming]

490
00:23:44,256 --> 00:23:45,799
Oh, thank you! [pants]

491
00:23:45,882 --> 00:23:47,801
- This way, this way.
- [screaming]

492
00:23:47,884 --> 00:23:51,888
[tense music continues]

493
00:23:51,972 --> 00:23:53,098
Are you okay?

494
00:23:53,181 --> 00:23:54,266
[gunshots]

495
00:23:54,349 --> 00:23:56,434
[people clamoring]

496
00:23:57,394 --> 00:24:00,480
[tense music swells]

497
00:24:07,571 --> 00:24:08,780
[thuds]

498
00:24:14,619 --> 00:24:19,791
[tense music swells]

499
00:24:25,338 --> 00:24:27,966
Jalil, I need to admit something to you.

500
00:24:28,049 --> 00:24:30,594
[Fatima] Wasn't he one of those
who attacked us?!

501
00:24:30,677 --> 00:24:33,138
And now you're protecting him?!

502
00:24:33,221 --> 00:24:35,807
Yes, if we fight, we don't give up.

503
00:24:35,891 --> 00:24:41,229
But winning also means we can show mercy.

504
00:24:41,313 --> 00:24:44,232
- [Felix] <i>How can we do our job…</i>
<i>- Gab!</i>

505
00:24:44,316 --> 00:24:46,067
…if you're blocking us?

506
00:24:46,151 --> 00:24:48,486
- Where is our child, sir?
- We're doing the best we can.

507
00:24:48,570 --> 00:24:49,988
Please calm down.

508
00:24:50,655 --> 00:24:52,407
[Gab] I didn't do anything to them.

509
00:24:52,490 --> 00:24:54,492
<i>But every day, they hurt me.</i>

510
00:24:54,576 --> 00:24:56,745
Gabriel, I'm going to help you.

511
00:24:56,828 --> 00:25:00,415
<i>At this moment, we can see</i>
<i>the suspect being talked to</i>

512
00:25:00,498 --> 00:25:03,335
<i>and being convinced to come down safely.</i>

513
00:25:03,919 --> 00:25:05,253
That's enough.

514
00:25:06,504 --> 00:25:08,215
Give that to me.

515
